# Basic Linux/Unix Commands

A list of important Linux/Unix commands every beginner should know.

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `cat` | Display file contents |
| `cd` | Change directory to dirname |
| `chgrp` | Change file group |
| `chmod` | Change file permissions |
| `cp` | Copy source file into destination |
| `file` | Determine file type |
| `find` | Find files |
| `grep` | Search files using regular expressions |
| `head` | Display first few lines of a file |
| `ln` | Create softlink on oldname |
| `ls` | Display information about file type |
| `mkdir` | Create a new directory |
| `more` | Display data in paginated form |
| `mv` | Move or rename files |
| `pwd` | Print current working directory |
| `rm` | Remove (delete) files |
| `rmdir` | Remove empty directory |
| `tail` | Print last few lines of a file |
| `touch` | Update file access and modification times |

---

Useful for beginners and system administrators alike.


